hange obstructs progress in urban planning</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>vii &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; An urban plan to reduce traffic</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">1.</span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-1 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"18\" name=\"question-1\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph&nbsp; A</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-1 explain-area-18\" data-qnumber=\"18\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 1 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">iii</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-18\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-18\" data-qnumber=\"18\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(18,1)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>&nbsp;Urban planning has a <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>long</strong></span> and <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>varied history</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>....is an <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>ancient one</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p>....<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>various planned</strong></span> communities (both theoretical and actual) were conceived</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>First sentence is the topic sentence of this paragraph. It indicates that urban planning happend in a very long time ago (acient one).</p>\n\n<p>In next supporting sentences, they give information about history of many planned communities (varied). So, <strong>heading iii</strong> is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">2.</span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-2 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"19\" name=\"question-2\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph&nbsp; B</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-2 explain-area-19\" data-qnumber=\"19\" data-qorder=\"2\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 2 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">v</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-19\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-19\" data-qnumber=\"19\" data-qorder=\"2\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(19,2)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The <span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>background </strong></span>to one <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>particular planned community&nbsp; </strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>...as a <span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>reaction to the pollution and crowding of the Industrial Revolution</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p>One of the most important <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>planned city concepts</strong></span>, the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Garden City</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This paragraph explains the progress of creating Gargen City. All sentences of this paragraph give information about the way garden city created - this could be seen in heading v - background to one particular planned community - Garden city.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>heading v</strong> is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">3.</span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-3 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"20\" name=\"question-3\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph&nbsp; C</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-3 explain-area-20\" data-qnumber=\"20\" data-qorder=\"3\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 3 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">vii</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-20\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-20\" data-qnumber=\"20\" data-qorder=\"3\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(20,3)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>An urban plan to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>reduce traffic&nbsp; </strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>...designed so that the residents would<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong> not require automobiles</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p>...which <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>shared 23 acres of commonly held parkland</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In highlighted sentences, we can see that this paragraph talks about the resident that would not require automobiles. Heading vii - An urban plan to reduce traffic - is the only heading that mention about traffic - automobiles.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>Heading vii</strong> is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">4.</span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-4 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"21\" name=\"question-4\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph&nbsp; D</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-4 explain-area-21\" data-qnumber=\"21\" data-qorder=\"4\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 4 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">iv</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-21\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-21\" data-qnumber=\"21\" data-qorder=\"4\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(21,4)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Financial problems</strong></span> helped <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>spread an urban planning concept</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>...following the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>stock market crash</strong></span> of 1929...</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In the first sentence of this paragraph, it talks about the stock market crash - means financial problems - and then, it leads to the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>creation of three towns. </strong></span></p>\n\n<p><strong>Heading iv</strong> is the correct answer because it mentions all about the financial crisis and the creation of three towns (spread an urban planning concept)</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n', 4, 2, 4, 3, 1, '2017-10-26 16:50:07', '2017-11-15 09:47:33');
INSERT INTO `reading_practice_lessons` (`id`, `title`, `level_user_id`, `content_lesson`, `content_highlight`, `image_feature`, `content_quiz`, `content_answer_quiz`, `total_questions`, `order_lesson`, `type_question_id`, `admin_responsibility`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(5, 'Practice 3', 2, '<p align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Public Libraries</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph A</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The word public comes from a Latin word, publicus, meaning people. A public library is for all the people in a community to use. It charges no fee for its services. The public library will have available, within the limits of its budget, a wide variety of books and other materials. These books or other materials may be borrowed, or taken out for a speciﬁc time, by anyone in the community. The library loans its materials.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph B</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Public libraries are usually tax-supported. There are a few that are instead supported from money that has been donated. And there are some that receive part of their money from taxes and part from gifts.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph C</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Few public libraries are exactly alike. Not only are the shapes and sizes of the buildings different, but so are the number of books and other materials in each. Your nearest library may be like the Los Angeles Public Library, which has over 4,538,458 books and bound periodicals (magazines and journals) in its collection. Or it may be like the Cherokee County Public library, which has only about 3,800 books in its collection.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph D</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Libraries vary in other ways, too, for instance, in the number of hours (or days) they are open or in the number of people who work there. Most public libraries, however,&nbsp; arrange their books and other materials in similar way. They divide their collection into two basic age groups, children and adult. Adult books are in one place; children&rsquo;s books are in another. Then the books are further separated by the kind of book. Storybooks - works of ﬁction - are separated from information, or fact books - nonﬁction.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph E</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">People often want to refer to, that is, look something up in a certain basic information book. Thus reference books, which are rarely read cover to cover, are put in a special place in the library, a reference section or perhaps a reference room. Reference books are never to be taken out of the library building.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph F</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Each library decides for itself how it should further arrange its books and other materials. In a large city library, certain nonﬁction materials may be put into a special area or separate room. For instance, there may be a separate room just for all the materials a library has on music. In another large city, the music materials might not be kept so separate. It would depend on what the people in that city had indicated they found useful.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph G</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">A library&rsquo;s holdings are everything the library has in its collection. These holdings almost always reﬂect the community&rsquo;s special interests. Suppose, for example, there were a town where Morgan horses were widely raised and trained. That town&rsquo;s library would most likely have a great deal of material about Morgan horses. Since the people who were interested in Morgan horses would probably be less interested in other breeds of horses, the library might have only a small amount of material on Mustangs or Appaloosas.</span></span></span></p>\n', '\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    <p align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Public Libraries</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph A</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The word public comes from a Latin word, publicus, meaning people. A public library is for all the people in a community to use. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-1 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509606652106\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"22\" id=\"hl-answer-22\">It charges no fee for its services</span>. The public library will have available, within the limits of its budget, a wide variety of books and other materials. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-1 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509606669179\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"22\" id=\"hl-answer-22\">These books or other materials may be borrowed, or taken out for a speciﬁc time, by anyone in the community.</span> The library loans its materials.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph B</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-2 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607021010\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"23\" id=\"hl-answer-23\">Public libraries are usually tax-supported</span>. There are a few that are instead supported <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-2 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607032890\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"23\" id=\"hl-answer-23\">from money that has been donated</span>. And there are some that receive part of their money <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-2 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607045482\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"23\" id=\"hl-answer-23\">from taxes and part from gifts.</span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph C</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Few public libraries are exactly alike. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-3 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607154170\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"24\" id=\"hl-answer-24\">Not only are the shapes and sizes of the buildings different, but so are the number of books and other materials in each.</span> Your nearest library may be like the Los Angeles Public Library, which has over 4,538,458 books and bound periodicals (magazines and journals) in its collection. Or it may be like the Cherokee County Public library, which has only about 3,800 books in its collection.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph D</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Libraries vary in other ways, too, for instance, in the number of hours (or days) they are open or in the number of people who work there. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-4 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607279866\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"25\" id=\"hl-answer-25\">Most public libraries, however,&nbsp; arrange their books and other materials in similar way. </span>They <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-4 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607298425\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"25\" id=\"hl-answer-25\">divide their collection into two basic age groups</span>, children and adult. Adult books are in one place; children’s books are in another. Then the <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-4 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607306474\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"25\" id=\"hl-answer-25\">books are further separated by the kind of book</span>. Storybooks - works of ﬁction - are <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-4 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607310129\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"25\" id=\"hl-answer-25\">separated from information, or fact books - nonﬁction.</span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph E</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">People often want to refer to, that is, look something up in a certain basic information book. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-5 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607430250\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"26\" id=\"hl-answer-26\">Thus reference books, which are rarely read cover to cover, are put in a special place in the library</span>, a reference section or perhaps a reference room. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-5 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607433057\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"26\" id=\"hl-answer-26\">Reference books are never to be taken out of the library building.</span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph F</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Each library decides for itself how it should further arrange its books and other materials. In a large city library, certain nonﬁction materials may be put into a special area or separate room. For instance, there may be a separate room just for all the materials a library has on music. In another large city, the music materials might not be kept so separate. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-6 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607599953\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"27\" id=\"hl-answer-27\">It would depend on what the people in that city had indicated they found useful.</span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Paragraph G</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">A library’s holdings are everything the library has in its collection. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-7 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509607786577\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"28\" id=\"hl-answer-28\">These holdings almost always reﬂect the community’s special interests.</span> Suppose, for example, there were a town where Morgan horses were widely raised and trained. That town’s library would most likely have a great deal of material about Morgan horses. Since the people who were interested in Morgan horses would probably be less interested in other breeds of horses, the library might have only a small amount of material on Mustangs or Appaloosas.</span></span></span></p>\n\n                                \n                                \n                                \n                                \n                                ', NULL, '<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><i>The reading passage <b>Public Libraries</b> has 7 paragraphs A-G. Choose the most suitable heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below. Write the appropriate numbers (<b>i-ix</b>). There are more headings than you can use.</i></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>i&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial support</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>ii&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Local decisions</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>iii&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Inﬂuence of people&#39;s interests</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>iv&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Materials about Morgan horses</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>v &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; History of public libraries</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>vi &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Certain books stay in the library</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>vii&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs