button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 1 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">vii</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-22\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-22\" data-qnumber=\"22\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(22,1)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Free services</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>for everyone&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>It charges <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>no fee for its services</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p>These books or other materials may be borrowed, or taken out for a speciﬁc time, <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>by anyone in the community</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This paragraph is about the way people borrowed books without any fee - it is totally free.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Heading vii</strong> is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">2. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-2 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"23\" name=\"question-2\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option><option value=\"viii\">viii</option><option value=\"ix\">ix</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph B</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-2 explain-area-23\" data-qnumber=\"23\" data-qorder=\"2\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 2 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">i</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-23\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-23\" data-qnumber=\"23\" data-qorder=\"2\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(23,2)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Financial support</strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>...Public libraries are usually <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>tax-supported</strong></span>...</p>\n\n			<p>...from <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>money </strong></span>that has been <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>donated</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p>...some that receive part of their money&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>from taxes and part from gifts</strong></span>.</p>\n\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The whole paragraph describes the way the public library get money - financial support.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>heading i </strong>is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">3. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-3 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"24\" name=\"question-3\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option><option value=\"viii\">viii</option><option value=\"ix\">ix</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph C</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-3 explain-area-24\" data-qnumber=\"24\" data-qorder=\"3\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 3 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">viii</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-24\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-24\" data-qnumber=\"24\" data-qorder=\"3\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(24,3)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>A <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\">wide </span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>Variety&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Not only </strong></span>are the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>shapes </strong></span>and <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>sizes </strong></span>of the buildings different, but so are the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>number of books</strong></span> and <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>other materials in each</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This paragraph is about the difference of many public libraries. Just take a look at all the headings, we only find heaidng viii mentions the wide variety of public library.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>heading viii</strong> is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">4. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-4 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"25\" name=\"question-4\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option><option value=\"viii\">viii</option><option value=\"ix\">ix</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph D</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-4 explain-area-25\" data-qnumber=\"25\" data-qorder=\"4\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 4 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">ix</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-25\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-25\" data-qnumber=\"25\" data-qorder=\"4\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(25,4)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Similar ways</strong></span> to <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>arrange books&nbsp;</strong></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Most public libraries, however,&nbsp; <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>arrange their books </strong></span>and other materials in <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>similar way</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>It is clear that this paragraph describes about the similar way that many public library use to arrange their books. Just read the highlighted sentences, you can find such ways.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">5. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-5 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"26\" name=\"question-5\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option><option value=\"viii\">viii</option><option value=\"ix\">ix</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph E</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-5 explain-area-26\" data-qnumber=\"26\" data-qorder=\"5\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 5 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">vi</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-26\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-26\" data-qnumber=\"26\" data-qorder=\"5\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(26,5)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Certain books </strong></span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>stay in the library&nbsp;</strong></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>look something up in a certain <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>basic information book.</strong></span>&nbsp;Thus <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>reference books</strong></span>, which are rarely read cover to cover, are <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>put in a special place</strong></span> in the library</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This paragraph concerns reference books, which are an certain kind of books that cannot be taken out of the library</p>\n\n<p><strong>Heading vi</strong> is the correct heading for this paragraph.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">6. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-6 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"27\" name=\"question-6\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option><option value=\"viii\">viii</option><option value=\"ix\">ix</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph F</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-6 explain-area-27\" data-qnumber=\"27\" data-qorder=\"6\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 6 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">ii</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-27\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-27\" data-qnumber=\"27\" data-qorder=\"6\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(27,6)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\">Local decisions</span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>It would depend on what the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\">people in that city had indicated they found useful</span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The last question of this paragraph leads us to the heading ii. This paragraph can be disturbed by heading ix - the way books were arranged, however, this paragraph describes nothing about \"similary ways\" - there is no comparison here.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">7. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-7 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"28\" name=\"question-7\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"i\">i</option><option value=\"ii\">ii</option><option value=\"iii\">iii</option><option value=\"iv\">iv</option><option value=\"v\">v</option><option value=\"vi\">vi</option><option value=\"vii\">vii</option><option value=\"viii\">viii</option><option value=\"ix\">ix</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Paragraph G</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-7 explain-area-28\" data-qnumber=\"28\" data-qorder=\"7\" data-type-question=\"4\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 7 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">iii</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-28\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-28\" data-qnumber=\"28\" data-qorder=\"7\" data-type-question=\"4\" onclick=\"showExplanation(28,7)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Inﬂuence </strong></span>of <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>people\'s interests&nbsp; </strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>These holdings almost always <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>reﬂect </strong></span>the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>community’s special interests</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The first two sentences give the main idea of this paragraph. \"reflect the community\'s interests\" equal to \"influence of poeple\'s interetss\". So, heading iii is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n', 7, 3, 4, 3, 1, '2017-10-26 16:53:42', '2017-11-15 10:03:35');
INSERT INTO `reading_practice_lessons` (`id`, `title`, `level_user_id`, `content_lesson`, `content_highlight`, `image_feature`, `content_quiz`, `content_answer_quiz`, `total_questions`, `order_lesson`, `type_question_id`, `admin_responsibility`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(6, 'Pracctice 4', 2, '<p align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Closing the Gender Gap</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Section A</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The beneﬁts of educating girls are enormous. By empowering women within their families and communities, education enables women to contribute more fully to the social and economic development of their societies. A girl&rsquo;s education is also an investment in future generations; the more educated a mother is, the more likely are her children to be educated.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Section B</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The educational level achieved by women has the most powerful inﬂuence on family size. The impact of education on family size is strongest and most consistent for women who have completed some secondary education. Educating girls is three times more likely than educating boys to lower family size. Education appears to affect family size in many ways. More educated women not only want fewer children than less educated ones, they are also more likely to marry and have children later, contributing to smaller family size. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Section C</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Unfortunately, in many low-income countries, investment in education has not kept up with the rapidly increasing school-age population. Many developing countries cut social spending during the 19805, putting more responsibility on families for financing education. Direct costs such as school fees, transportation, uniforms and books make it more difficult for poor families to educate all their children and parents in many countries give priority to sons.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Section D </b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Parents may see limited economic beneﬁts in educating daughters. In many countries, girls are more likely than their brothers to he kept home to perform household chores, including caring for younger children, For these and other reasons, including early marriage and pregnancy, dropout rates for girls also tend to be higher than those for boys. In some cultures, parents are reluctant to allow their daughters to travel long distances to school, to be taught by male teachers and to enroll in schools without separate activities for girls.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Section E</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Efforts to increase female enrolment levels must recognise the complex factors limiting educational opportunities for girls, as well as their continued enrolment once within the school system. Building more schools is often important to expand educational opportunities for girls, But especially in poor countries, more efficient use of existing resources for education could make possible the enrolment of more girls. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Section F</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Hiring more female teachers and providing separate facilities for girls can help to overcome cultural barriers. In some countries, ﬁnancial assistance such as scholarships for girls has also proved successful in encouraging parents to keep their daughters in school. Flexible school schedules can help to accommodate girls who have to work at home. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Section G</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Providing access to good quality family planning services remains the most effective way to lower population growth rates in developing countries. Average family size and child death rates are lowest, however, in countries that combine strong family planning and health programmes with&nbsp; levels of education for women.</span></span></span></p>\n', '\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    <p align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Closing the Gender Gap</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>Section A</b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:150%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-1 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509640411415\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"29\" id=\"hl-answer-29\">The beneﬁts of educating girls are enormous</span>. By empowering women within their families and communities, education enables women to c<span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-1 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509640421118\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"29\" id=\"hl-answer-29\">ontribute more fully to the social and economic development of their societies</span>. A girl’s education is also an investment in future generations; <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-1 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509640605366\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123)