 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"62\" id=\"hl-answer-62\">‘his great skill consisted, like Socrates, in helping us to learn and think for ourselves’</span> (Markham, 1967). When Jowett took up the mantle of Vice-Chancellor of&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Oxford University in 1882, his teaching method of Socratic dialogue became established as a ‘pattern for the whole university’ (Markham, 1967).</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b>C)</b> In the last decade, multiple studies have been conducted <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-1 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509933458911\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"61\" id=\"hl-answer-61\">exploring the unique learning benefits of the tutorial method</span>. 130 years after it was formally established as the cornerstone of <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-1 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509933470567\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"61\" id=\"hl-answer-61\">Oxford education, the tutorial method retains its prestige and effectiveness.</span> <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-3 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509934017680\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"63\" id=\"hl-answer-63\">As the present university website states, it is through the tutorial system that ‘students develop powers of independent and critical thought, analytical and&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-3 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1509934017680\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"63\" id=\"hl-answer-63\">problem-solving abilities, and skills in both written and oral communication and argument.</span></span></span></span></p>\n\n                                \n                                \n                                \n                                \n                                \n                                ', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><i>Which paragraph contains the information in the statements below?</i></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">1. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-1 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"61\" name=\"question-1\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"A\">A</option><option value=\"B\">B</option><option value=\"C\">C</option><option value=\"D\">D</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">The tutorial is still a key part of the Oxford education system.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">2. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-2 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"62\" name=\"question-2\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"A\">A</option><option value=\"B\">B</option><option value=\"C\">C</option><option value=\"D\">D</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">The tutorial method encourages students to learn independently.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">3. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-3 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"63\" name=\"question-3\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"A\">A</option><option value=\"B\">B</option><option value=\"C\">C</option><option value=\"D\">D</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">The tutorial method features in Oxford University marketing.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">4. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-4 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"64\" name=\"question-4\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"A\">A</option><option value=\"B\">B</option><option value=\"C\">C</option><option value=\"D\">D</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Traditionally, Oxford tutors had more than just an academic role.</span></span></span></p>\n', '<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><i>Which paragraph contains the information in the statements below?</i></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">1. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-1 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"61\" name=\"question-1\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"A\">A</option><option value=\"B\">B</option><option value=\"C\">C</option><option value=\"D\">D</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">The tutorial is still a key part of the Oxford education system.</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-1 explain-area-61\" data-qnumber=\"61\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"5\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 1 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">C</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-61\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-61\" data-qnumber=\"61\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"5\" onclick=\"showExplanation(61,1)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>tutorial is still a key part</strong></span> of the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Oxford education </strong></span>system&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>130 years after it was formally established as the cornerstone of&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Oxford education</strong></span>, <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>the tutorial method retains its prestige and effectiveness</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Paragraph C have these information in highlighted senteces. Only this paragraph describes the importance of tutorial method in Oxford edution.</p>\n\n<p>Paragraph A also gives information about tutorial method, but it does not says: tutorial is still a key..., it only describes about it. So, section A is not the correct answer</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">2. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-2 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"62\" name=\"question-2\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"A\">A</option><option value=\"B\">B</option><option value=\"C\">C</option><option value=\"D\">D</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">The tutorial method encourages students to learn independently.</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-2 explain-area-62\" data-qnumber=\"62\" data-qorder=\"2\" data-type-question=\"5\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 2 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">B</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-62\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-62\" data-qnumber=\"62\" data-qorder=\"2\" data-type-question=\"5\" onclick=\"showExplanation(62,2)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The tutorial method encourages students to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>learn independently.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>‘his great skill consisted, like Socrates, in helping us to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>learn and think for ourselves</strong></span>’</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>You can scan for the synonyms in paragraph&nbsp;B: Think for ourselves ~ learn independently.</p>\n\n<p>So, paragraph B is the correct answer for this question.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">3. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-3 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"63\" name=\"question-3\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"A\">A</option><option value=\"B\">B</option><option value=\"C\">C</option><option value=\"D\">D</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">The tutorial method features in Oxford University marketing.</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-3 explain-area-63\" data-qnumber=\"63\" data-qorder=\"3\" data-type-question=\"5\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 3 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">C</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-63\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-63\" data-qnumber=\"63\" data-qorder=\"3\" data-type-question=\"5\" onclick=\"showExplanation(63,3)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The tutorial method features in <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Oxford University marketing.</strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>As the present university <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>website states</strong></span>, it is through the tutorial system that ‘students develop powers of independent and critical thought, analytical and&nbsp;problem-solving abilities, and skills in both written and oral communication and argument.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In highlighted sentences of paragraph C, you can see that tutorial method is used in their website to promote the learning method of Oxford University. This is one way of marketing, so paragraph C is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">4. </span></span></span><select class=\"question-quiz question-select question-4 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"64\" name=\"question-4\" disabled=\"disabled\"><option value=\"\"></option><option value=\"A\">A</option><option value=\"B\">B</option><option value=\"C\">C</option><option value=\"D\">D</option></select> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Traditionally, Oxford tutors had more than just an academic role.</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-4 explain-area-64\" data-qnumber=\"64\" data-qorder=\"4\" data-type-question=\"5\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 4 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">A</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-64\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-64\" data-qnumber=\"64\" data-qorder=\"4\" data-type-question=\"5\" onclick=\"showExplanation(64,4)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Traditionally</strong></span>, Oxford tutors had <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>more than just an academic role.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Oxford <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>since the 11th century</strong></span>, and the role of tutors wasdocumented<strong> </strong><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>in the 15<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;century</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p>Thus, the early role of the tutor was<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong> both pastoral as well as&nbsp;academic.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The last sentence of paragraph A is about this information. We can read the previous sentence, this method is used in long time ago, can be seen as traditionally.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>paragraph A </strong>is the correct answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n', 4, 2, 5, 3, 1, '2017-10-27 11:11:57', '2017-11-15 11:34:11');
