rong>D</strong></span> <input class=\"question-quiz question-radio question-1 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"134\" name=\"question-1\" onclick=\"bitest(this)\" type=\"radio\" value=\"D\" disabled=\"disabled\"> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">It has several moons.</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-1 explain-area-134\" data-qnumber=\"134\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"6\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 1 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">C</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-134\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-134\" data-qnumber=\"134\" data-qorder=\"1\" data-type-question=\"6\" onclick=\"showExplanation(134,1)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><i>Why is it thought that the planet may <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>be able to support life</strong></span>?</i></p>\n\n			<p>B: It is <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>42 light years from the Sun</strong></span>.<i>..&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</i></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>A new ‘super-Earth’ has been discovered that could have a<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong> life-supporting climate and water</strong></span>.</p>\n\n			<p>was discovered in a multi-world solar&nbsp;system 4<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>2 light years from the Sun</strong></span>...</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>A is wrong answer because in the first sentence of this passage, author only indicates that this planet could have a life-suporting climate and water, it does not mean that this planet alreay has water in it.</p>\n\n<p>C &amp; D give the right information about this planet, but they are not the main explaination for this question.</p>\n\n<p>B is the correct answer. You can find those information in highlighted answer.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><i>2. Which statement is true of the “Goldilocks” zone?</i></b></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span class=\"label-radio key-label\"><strong>A</strong></span> <input class=\"question-quiz question-radio question-2 \" data-qnumber=\"135\" name=\"question-2\" onclick=\"bitest(this)\" type=\"radio\" value=\"A\" disabled=\"disabled\"> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">It is the region of a planet which has a habitable climate.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span class=\"label-radio key-label\"><strong>B</strong></span> <input class=\"question-quiz question-radio question-2 \" data-qnumber=\"135\" name=\"question-2\" onclick=\"bitest(this)\" type=\"radio\" value=\"B\" disabled=\"disabled\"> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">It refers to a zone which is too close to the parent star.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span class=\"label-radio key-label\"><strong>C</strong></span> <input class=\"question-quiz question-radio question-2 \" data-qnumber=\"135\" name=\"question-2\" onclick=\"bitest(this)\" type=\"radio\" value=\"C\" disabled=\"disabled\"> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">It refers to a planet with several moons and a long orbit.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span class=\"label-radio key-label\"><strong>D</strong></span> <input class=\"question-quiz question-radio question-2 last-option\" data-qnumber=\"135\" name=\"question-2\" onclick=\"bitest(this)\" type=\"radio\" value=\"D\" disabled=\"disabled\"> <span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">It is an orbit region which is comparable to the Earth’s.</span></span></span></p><div class=\"explain-area explain-2 explain-area-135\" data-qnumber=\"135\" data-qorder=\"2\" data-type-question=\"6\"><div class=\"show-answer\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-danger btn-show-answer\">Answer 2 <div class=\"badge badge-pill key-answer\">D</div></button><div class=\"explain-show\" id=\"explain-135\"> <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-show-explanation show-explanation-135\" data-qnumber=\"135\" data-qorder=\"2\" data-type-question=\"6\" onclick=\"showExplanation(135,2)\"><i class=\"fa fa-key\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explanation</button><div class=\"hidden explanation\"><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><i>Which statement is true of the “<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Goldilocks</strong></span>” zone?</i></p>\n\n			<p>D: It is<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong> an orbit region which is comparable to the Earth’s</strong></span>.<i>..&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</i></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Just as <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Goldilocks </strong></span>liked her porridge to be neither too hot nor too cold but just right, this planet or indeed any moons that is has lie <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>in an orbit comparable to Earth...</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>A is wrong, because in this paragraph, you can see that Goldilocks zone only has the probability of being habitable.</p>\n\n<p>B &amp; C provice unclear information about this zone.</p>\n\n<p>D is the correct answer, you can find those information clearly in highlighted sentence.</p>\n</div></div></div></div>\n\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</p>\n', 2, 4, 6, 3, 1, '2017-11-06 15:05:39', '2017-11-15 14:59:42');
