ssful? The answer depends on how much of a threat or challenge it appears to be. <span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-6 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1510124754498\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"173\" id=\"hl-answer-173\">Circumstances that bring a threat or challenge to a person’s sense of well-being produce stress. Those that do not threaten or challenge us are not stressful.</span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Looking at stress this way gives us a general definition of the concept of stress: Stress is a response to circumstances that seem threatening or challenging. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The circumstances that cause stress vary from one person to another. It all depends on show we appraise circumstances.<span class=\"answer-highlight highlight-7 hidden-highlight\" data-timestamp=\"1510124867297\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 123);\" data-highlighted=\"true\" data-qnumber=\"174\" id=\"hl-answer-174\"> In addition, the things that cause us stress today may not cause us stress at another time. And the opposite is true: things that once caused no stress may now be stressful.</span></span></span></span></p>\n\n                                \n                                \n                                \n                                ', NULL, '<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">Read the passage What Is Stress? and look at the following statements. Write</span></span></span></strong></p>\n\n<p sty