(1260, 10, 1, 5, 60, 'B', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong> percentage of UK tourism jobs </strong></span>based in and around <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>London </strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>over 15 per cent </strong></span>of all tourism-related jobs in the UK were based in <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>London</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This is only paragraph mention about London. When we do this question, try to scan for &quot;London&quot; in this passage.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 11:18:26', '2017-11-15 11:18:26'),
(1261, 11, 1, 5, 61, 'C', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>tutorial is still a key part</strong></span> of the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Oxford education </strong></span>system&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>130 years after it was formally established as the cornerstone of&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Oxford education</strong></span>, <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>the tutorial method retains its prestige and effectiveness</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Paragraph C have these information in highlighted senteces. Only this paragraph describes the importance of tutorial method in Oxford edution.</p>\n\n<p>Paragraph A also gives information about tutorial method, but it does not says: tutorial is still a key..., it only describes about it. So, section A is not the correct answer</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 11:34:11', '2017-11-15 11:34:11'),
(1262, 11, 1, 5, 62, 'B', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The tutorial method encourages students to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>learn independently.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>&lsquo;his great skill consisted, like Socrates, in helping us to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>learn and think for ourselves</strong></span>&rsquo;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>You can scan for the synonyms in paragraph&nbsp;B: Think for ourselves ~ learn independently.</p>\n\n<p>So, paragraph B is the correct answer for this question.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 11:34:11', '2017-11-15 11:34:11'),
(1263, 11, 1, 5, 63, 'C', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The tutorial method features in <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Oxford University marketing.</strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>As the present university <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>website states</strong></span>, it is through the tutorial system that &lsquo;students develop powers of independent and critical thought, analytical and&nbsp;problem-solving abilities, and skills in both written and oral communication and argument.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In highlighted sentences of paragraph C, you can see that tutorial method is used in their website to promote the learning method of Oxford University. This is one way of marketing, so paragraph C is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 11:34:11', '2017-11-15 11:34:11'),
(1264, 11, 1, 5, 64, 'A', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Traditionally</strong></span>, Oxford tutors had <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>more than just an academic role.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Oxford <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>since the 11th century</strong></span>, and the role of tutors wasdocumented<strong> </strong><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>in the 15<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;century</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p>Thus, the early role of the tutor was<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong> both pastoral as well as&nbsp;academic.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The last sentence of paragraph A is about this information. We can read the previous sentence, this method is used in long time ago, can be seen as traditionally.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>paragraph A </strong>is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 11:34:11', '2017-11-15 11:34:11'),
(1265, 12, 1, 5, 65, 'C', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>This is possibly <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>inconvenient for car owners.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>There is<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong> no space for parking</strong></span> nearby.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Skim this passage first and we can see that in paragraph C - Hanley house - there is no space for parking nearby - obviously it is not convenient for car owners.</p>\n\n<p>Only Hanley house has no parking areas nearby. So, paragraph C is the correct answer for this information</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:02:38', '2017-11-15 14:02:38'),
(1266, 12, 1, 5, 66, 'A', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>This is <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>best</strong></span> if you <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>like surfing the Web.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Broadband Internet connections</strong></span>&nbsp;and telephones...</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>You have to brainstorm that web related to the internet. Because in this paggase, there is no information about web, only paragraph A give information about broadband internet connection, it means that this house would be good for surfing the web.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>paragraph A</strong> is the correct answer of this question.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:02:38', '2017-11-15 14:02:38'),
(1267, 12, 1, 5, 67, 'D', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Of the College residences, this has the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>fewest students</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>...and housing&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>120 students&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Just make comparison between those hose, we can see that Glencarrick house has the fewest students.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>paragraph D</strong> is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:02:38', '2017-11-15 14:02:38'),
(1268, 12, 1, 5, 69, 'B', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>You have to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>organise parking a year at a time.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Parking is available</strong></span> with permits costing &pound;90 <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>for the academic year.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The last sentece of paragraph B gives information about this. Only Student Village requires this action.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:02:38', '2017-11-15 14:02:38'),
(1269, 12, 1, 5, 70, 'D', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>This accommodation does <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>not belong to the College.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><strong>GLENCARRICK HOUSE</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;a <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>privately-owned&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This house is a privately-owned.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:02:38', '2017-11-15 14:02:38'),
(1270, 12, 1, 5, 71, 'C', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Here you definitely <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>do not have your own bathroom.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Eighteen rooms per floor with <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>communal </strong></span>kitchens, lounges, <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>bathrooms</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Communal means belonging to or used by a group of people rather than one single person.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>paragraph C</strong> is the correct answer for this question.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:02:38', '2017-11-15 14:02:38'),
(1271, 12, 1, 5, 125, 'D', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>This is a option <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>offered</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>by the College&nbsp;</strong></span> &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Rooms are <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>allocated</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>by the College Accommodation Service</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This rooms are allocated by the college, means that this rooms are offered by the college.</p>\n\n<p>So, <strong>paragraph D</strong> is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:02:38', '2017-11-15 14:02:38'),
(1272, 13, 1, 5, 72, 'B', '<table cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" order=\"1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>It is <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>awarded on results</strong></span> obtained in the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>SCE exam</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>....<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>to the three most outstanding</strong></span> State Certificate of Education <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>(SCE) students</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Scanning for SCE, you can find the information about it in category B &amp; E. However, category E indicates that this scholarship is not awarded based on SEC results.</p>\n\n<p>So, B is the correct answer</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:12:54', '2017-11-15 14:12:54'),
(1273, 13, 1, 5, 73, 'A', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>It is only available to students from the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>College&#39;s overseas branch.</strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>One scholarship of A$2000 for the most outstanding students entering the Foundation Studies Program from each of the following countries: <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Singapore, Malaysia and Thailand. </strong></span>An additional six scholarships are available for students from <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>other countries</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This scholarship is offered only to some asian countries such as Singapore, Malaysia and Thailand....</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:12:54', '2017-11-15 14:12:54'),
(1274, 13, 1, 5, 74, 'F', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>It is <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>not offered every year&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>his scholarship <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>is offered every second year...</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This category scholarship is offered every second years, not every year.</p>\n\n<p>So, F is the correct answer</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:12:54', '2017-11-15 14:12:54'),
(1275, 13, 1, 5, 75, 'E', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Students <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>need to apply</strong></span> for it&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Note that applicants <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>need to apply for this scholarship</strong></span> on the Bramley College International Scholarship Application Form.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Only this category requires students to apply. Others will award based on the result of previous semester or a specific certificate.</p>\n\n<p>So, E is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:12:54', '2017-11-15 14:12:54'),
(1276, 13, 1, 5, 76, 'A', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>It is offered <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>twice each year&nbsp; &nbsp; </strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>These scholarships are offered <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>on two dates</strong></span>, to students <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>in the March</strong></span> and <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>June </strong></span>intakes of the program</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>These scholarships are offered on two dates - means twice a year.</p>\n\n<p>Category A is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:12:54', '2017-11-15 14:12:54'),
(1277, 13, 1, 5, 77, 'F', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>It pays <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>100% of the student&#39;s tuition fees</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>One <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>full-fee scholarship</strong></span>&nbsp;to the most outstanding student&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>It is clear that this is full-fee scholarship (means 100% fee).</p>\n\n<p>As the result, F is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:12:54', '2017-11-15 14:12:54'),
(1278, 13, 1, 5, 78, 'G', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>It provides <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>50% of </strong></span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>one year&#39;s fees&nbsp;</strong></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Four&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>half-fee scholarships</strong></span>&nbsp;to outstanding students of&nbsp; Bramley College&#39;s Singapore campus<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong> for the final year </strong></span>of the two-year Certificate.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Half-fee means 50%. The remaining scholarship is not offer 50%.</p>\n\n<p>So, G is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:12:54', '2017-11-15 14:12:54'),
