(1330, 25, 1, 6, 134, 'C', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><i>Why is it thought that the planet may <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>be able to support life</strong></span>?</i></p>\n\n			<p>B: It is <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>42 light years from the Sun</strong></span>.<i>..&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</i></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>A new &lsquo;super-Earth&rsquo; has been discovered that could have a<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong> life-supporting climate and water</strong></span>.</p>\n\n			<p>was discovered in a multi-world solar&nbsp;system 4<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>2 light years from the Sun</strong></span>...</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>A is wrong answer because in the first sentence of this passage, author only indicates that this planet could have a life-suporting climate and water, it does not mean that this planet alreay has water in it.</p>\n\n<p>C &amp; D give the right information about this planet, but they are not the main explaination for this question.</p>\n\n<p>B is the correct answer. You can find those information in highlighted answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:59:42', '2017-11-15 14:59:42'),
(1331, 25, 1, 6, 135, 'D', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><i>Which statement is true of the &ldquo;<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Goldilocks</strong></span>&rdquo; zone?</i></p>\n\n			<p>D: It is<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong> an orbit region which is comparable to the Earth&rsquo;s</strong></span>.<i>..&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</i></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Just as <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Goldilocks </strong></span>liked her porridge to be neither too hot nor too cold but just right, this planet or indeed any moons that is has lie <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>in an orbit comparable to Earth...</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>A is wrong, because in this paragraph, you can see that Goldilocks zone only has the probability of being habitable.</p>\n\n<p>B &amp; C provice unclear information about this zone.</p>\n\n<p>D is the correct answer, you can find those information clearly in highlighted sentence.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 14:59:42', '2017-11-15 14:59:42'),
(1332, 27, 1, 6, 140, 'B', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The factor which decides <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>the order of importance </strong></span>or the main elements required for survival is:</p>\n\n			<p>B: <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>your location</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Their <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>order of importance </strong></span>will depend upon <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>where you happen to be.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Answer for this question can be found in the first paragraph: &quot;...where you happen to be&quot;. So, B is the correct answer.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:24:26', '2017-11-15 15:24:26'),
(1333, 27, 1, 6, 141, 'A', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The basic need that may NOT be equally important as the others in <span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>extremely cold places</strong></span>?:</p>\n\n			<p><strong>A</strong>&nbsp;water.</p>\n\n			<p><strong>B</strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>shelter</strong></span>.</p>\n\n			<p><strong>C</strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>fire</strong></span>.</p>\n\n			<p>.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Shelter </strong></span>will often be the prime necessity in extremes of climate or temperatures such as in the <span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>frozen polar regions</strong></span> or in the baking deserts.&nbsp;The need for <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>fire</strong></span> is closely linked&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In 2 last sentences of paragraph 2, It onlyindicates the need of shelter &amp; fire, there is no mention about water here.</p>\n\n<p>So, A is the correct answer</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:24:26', '2017-11-15 15:24:26'),
(1334, 27, 1, 6, 142, 'D', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Fire </strong></span>is described as:</p>\n\n			<p>D: closely <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>linked with shelter</strong></span>.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>The need for <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>fire </strong></span>is <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>closely linked</strong></span>. (with shelter - that is mentionted in previous sentence)</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The answer for this question can be found in the last sentence of second paragraph.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:24:26', '2017-11-15 15:24:26'),
(1335, 27, 1, 6, 143, 'B', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>B: People may <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>die</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>quickly </strong></span>in the<span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong> water of polar regions</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>death </strong></span>comes <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>in only minutes</strong></span> in the <span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>icy waters of the poles</strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>A is wrong, based on the second paragraph, exposure to wind can be fatal.</p>\n\n<p>C is wrong because in the third sentence of paragraph 2, we can see that: Food is rarely the first priority (rarely means not often)</p>\n\n<p>D is wrong, based on the information in the third paragraph: water is always universally important.</p>\n\n<p>B is the correct answer, you can find this information in the first highlighted sentence of second paragraph.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:24:26', '2017-11-15 15:24:26'),
(1336, 30, 1, 7, 153, 'FALSE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Africa had the <span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>warmest July</strong></span> day ever on <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>July 1</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>According to the Met Office, the UK had its warmest July day ever on <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>July 1</strong></span>.</p>\n\n			<p>...while&nbsp;the African continent had the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>second-warmest July </strong></span><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>(NOT WARMEST)</strong></span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span>on record..</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In the last sentence of paragraph 1, it indicates that on july 1, african continent had the second-warmest, not the warmest.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is False.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:45:49', '2017-11-15 15:45:49'),
(1337, 30, 1, 7, 154, 'TRUE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>temperature is rising</strong></span> due to the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>increased level of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>While&nbsp;the impact of <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>increased levels of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere</strong></span> is a <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>key driver of rising temperatures...</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This information is quite clear in the first sentence of second paragraph.</p>\n\n<p>This paragraph indicates two main reasons for increasing temperatures are carbon dioxide and El Nino.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:45:49', '2017-11-15 15:45:49'),
(1338, 30, 1, 7, 155, 'TRUE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>2015 </strong></span>might be the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>hottest year</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>in the history.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>many experts believe that <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>2015 </strong></span>will be the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>warmest year on record </strong></span>by some margin.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>It&#39;s quite easy to do this question, You just need to scan for &quot;2015&quot; in the passage. In the third paragraph, you can find the information (in highlighted sentence)</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is TRUE.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:45:49', '2017-11-15 15:45:49'),
(1339, 30, 1, 7, 156, 'NOT GIVEN', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Record warming was recorded in various seas, such as <span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>Black and Azov Sea.&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>with record warming in large expanses of the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Pacific and Indian Oceans&nbsp;</strong></span><strong>(Not mention about Black and Azov Sea)</strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In fourth paragrpah, it provides the information of the recording in Pacific and Indian Oceans, however, there is no information about Black and Azov Sea.</p>\n\n<p>This statement is clearly Not Given</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:45:49', '2017-11-15 15:45:49'),
(1340, 30, 1, 7, 157, 'TRUE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The year 2015 <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>might </strong></span>very well consist of a number of <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>very warm months.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>...means <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>there is the&nbsp;potential</strong></span> to see some <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>very warm months </strong></span>throughout this year - as the new figures for July appear to show.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>For this statement, we can find the information in the last paragraph. In this paragraph, author mentions: there is the potential (means might...)</p>\n\n<p>This statement is true.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:45:49', '2017-11-15 15:45:49'),
(1341, 31, 1, 7, 158, 'NOT GIVEN', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Friends of the Earth Trust</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>organises </strong></span>lots of activities to <span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>help people understand the environmental problems.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Friends of the Earth Trust</strong></span> is an educational charily <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>set up</strong></span> to help people of all ages <span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>become aware of the threats to our environment.</strong></span></p>\n\n			<p><span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>(Not mention about any activites)</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Only frist paragraph talks about Friends of the Earth Trust, however, it does not give any information about activites organised by this group.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is Not Given.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:55:46', '2017-11-15 15:55:46'),
(1342, 31, 1, 7, 159, 'NO', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>The forest cut down every year to make paper in Britain is <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>bigger than the size of Wales is.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Every year a <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>forest the size of Wales</strong></span> is cut down to make paper for use In Britain.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The first sentence of third paragraph, we can see that: a forest size of Wales....means that the area of forest that is cut down is equal to Wales, not bigger.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is No.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:55:46', '2017-11-15 15:55:46'),
(1343, 31, 1, 7, 160, 'YES', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Using recycled paper and saving energy in buildings</strong></span> can both <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>create new jobs.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>New jobs would also be created </strong></span>if there was a large programme to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>save energy in buildings.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In the first sentence of fourth paragraph gives us the information about this.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is clearly Yes.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:55:46', '2017-11-15 15:55:46'),
(1344, 31, 1, 7, 161, 'NOT GIVEN', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>It is more <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>difficult</strong></span> to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>save energy than to produce it.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>It is <span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>cheaper</strong></span><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong> (Not mention difficult)</strong>&nbsp;</span>to <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>save energy than to produce electricity</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In fourth paragraph, it only gives information that saving energy is cheaper than producing electricity, there is no mentions about the difficulty.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is Not Given.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:55:46', '2017-11-15 15:55:46'),
(1345, 31, 1, 7, 162, 'YES', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>People can <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>reduce pollution and traffic jams</strong></span> by <span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>using more bicycles</strong></span> on short journeys.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Energy could also be saved if more short journeys were <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>made by bicycle.</strong></span> This would <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>reduce pollution and traffic congestion.&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In the last sentence of this passage and last sentences of fourth paragraph, you can find the information of this statement.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is Yes</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 15:55:46', '2017-11-15 15:55:46'),
(1346, 32, 1, 7, 163, 'NOT GIVEN', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Astronomers <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>often</strong> </span></span>find <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>something odd</strong></span> on the sky.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>More than ten years ago, while taking the temperature of the universe, astronomers found <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>something odd</strong></span>.</p>\n\n			<p>Not mention about &quot;often&quot;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>First sentence of this paragraph gives information that astronomers found something odd. However, there is no information about &quot;often&quot;.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is <strong>not given</strong> in this passage.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:05:15', '2017-11-15 16:05:15'),
(1347, 32, 1, 7, 164, 'TRUE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>The CMB</strong></span> is the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>thermal radiation</strong></span> across the entire universe.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>The astronomers were measuring the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>thermal radiation </strong></span>that bathes the entire universe, a glowing relic of the big bang. To gaze at this <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>cosmic microwave background</strong></span>, or <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>CMB</strong></span>......</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In the first 2 sentences of paragraph 2, you can find out that CMB is the thermal radiation.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:05:15', '2017-11-15 16:05:15'),
(1348, 32, 1, 7, 165, 'FALSE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>The CMB</strong></span> varies from <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>extremely low to very high temperatures</strong></span>.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>The CMB</strong></span> blankets the sky, and looks pretty much the same everywhere,<span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong> existing at a feebly cold temperature of 2.725 kelvins - just a couple degrees warmer than absolute zero.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In third paragraph, we can see that the fluctuations of CMB is very tiny (one part in 100,000), and it exists in a very cold temperature, so this statement is False</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:05:15', '2017-11-15 16:05:15'),
(1349, 32, 1, 7, 166, 'TRUE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Investigation of <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>fluctuations of temperature</strong></span> in the space <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>help scientists to understand</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>what the cosmos is made of.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>those random fluctuations</strong></span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong> help scientists understand </strong></span><span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>what the cosmos is made of</strong></span> and how it all came to be.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>This information is quite clear in highlighted sentence.</p>\n\n<p>This statement is True</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:05:15', '2017-11-15 16:05:15'),
(1350, 32, 1, 7, 167, 'NOT GIVEN', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>The cosmic supervoid </strong></span>is the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>largest structure in the universe.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>...<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>cosmic supervoid</strong></span>, so big that it <span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>might be</strong></span></span> the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>largest structure in the universe.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In last sentence of fourth paragraph, the author indicates that cosmic supervoid <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>MIGHT BE</strong></span> the largest structure.</p>\n\n<p>There is no certain conclusion about this theory, just a guess. So, this statement is Not Give.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:05:15', '2017-11-15 16:05:15'),
(1351, 33, 1, 7, 168, 'FALSE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Knowing our feelings about stress</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>can explain</strong></span> what causes the stress. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>But <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>knowing how we feel when we experience stress</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">does not explain it</span></strong></span>; nor does it tell us what causes it.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The last sentence of second paragraph expalins that knowing what we exprerience stress can not explain about stress.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is False</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:17:39', '2017-11-15 16:17:39'),
(1352, 33, 1, 7, 169, 'NOT GIVEN', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>Bothersome noises</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">are more likely to cause stress</span></strong></span> than <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>a poor test performance</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>A deadline, <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>a poor test performance</strong></span>, or <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>bothersome noises</strong></span> all may be thought of as stressors.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>There is <strong>no comparison</strong> between poor test performance and bothersome noises in this paragraph.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is Not Given</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:17:39', '2017-11-15 16:17:39'),
(1353, 33, 1, 7, 170, 'NOT GIVEN', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Negative events</strong></span> cause <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">more stress </span></strong></span>than <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>positive ones</strong></span> do.</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Stress, then, can be caused by both <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>negative and positive events&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Again, there is no comparison between negative events and positive invents in ways of creating stress.</p>\n\n<p>So, this statement is Not Given</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:17:39', '2017-11-15 16:17:39'),
(1354, 33, 1, 7, 171, 'TRUE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Sometimes whether an <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>event is negative or not </strong></span>is <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>based on</strong></span> a <span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>personal decision.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Of course, whether <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>an event is thought of as positive or negative is</strong></span>, in some ways, <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>a matter of </strong></span><span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>personal choice.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In highlighted sentence, we can find information for this statement.</p>\n\n<p>A matter of personal choice means personal decision. So, this statement is True</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:17:39', '2017-11-15 16:17:39'),
(1355, 33, 1, 7, 172, 'TRUE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Whether an event is considered stressful</strong></span> may be determined by the <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>way people interpret it.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>In sum, it is <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>the way people interpret </strong></span>an event that makes it <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>stressful or not stressful.&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The first sentence of fifth paragraph provides this information.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:17:39', '2017-11-15 16:17:39'),
(1356, 33, 1, 7, 173, 'FALSE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Sometimes those circumstances that <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>are not threatening to us</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>are also stressful.</strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Circumstances that bring a threat or challenge to a person&rsquo;s sense of well-being produce stress. <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Those that do not threaten</strong></span> or challenge us <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">are NOT&nbsp;stressful.</span></strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The answer can be found in last sentence of sixth paragraph. This statement will be true if it said that: sometimes those circumstances that are not threatening to us <strong>ARE NOT STREESFUL</strong></p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:17:39', '2017-11-15 16:17:39'),
(1357, 33, 1, 7, 174, 'TRUE', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>An event or situation</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>may not always be a stressor.&nbsp; &nbsp; </strong></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>In addition, <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>the things</strong></span> that cause us stress today <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>may not cause us stress at another time. </strong></span>And the opposite is true: <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>things </strong></span>that <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>once caused no stress may now be stressful.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Last paragraph expalins this idea quite clearly.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:17:39', '2017-11-15 16:17:39'),
(1358, 34, 1, 8, 179, 'veins//vein', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Look at the picture&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>If you look <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>closer at leave</strong></span>s, you will notice<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong> networks of thin threads</strong></span>. Those networks are called <span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>veins</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>If you skim the first 3 paragraphs, you can find out that:</p>\n\n<p>First paragraph just gives the overview of plant&#39;s benefits. So, this paragraph will not suitable for finding answer for this question.</p>\n\n<p>Second and third paragraph is about the introduction of tree. But it only describes about photosynthesis</p>\n\n<p>Just take a look at paragraph 4, they gives details information of leaf and here we find our answer for question 1</p>\n\n<p>The answer of question is on the highlighted sentence. The answer is <strong>Vein</strong>/ or <strong>Veins</strong></p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:36:40', '2017-11-15 16:36:40'),
(1359, 34, 1, 8, 180, 'midrib', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Look at the picture&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>The main vein of a leaf, <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>running down the centre of the leaf</strong></span>, is called midrib.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The second arrow points to a large vein in the centre of the leaf. The last sentence of the fourth paragraph says: The main vein of a leaf, running down the centre of the leaf, is called midrib.</p>\n\n<p>So the correct answer is: <strong>midrib</strong>.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:36:40', '2017-11-15 16:36:40'),
(1360, 34, 1, 8, 181, 'blade', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>&nbsp;Look at the picture&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>The blade is the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>broad, flat part of the leaf</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Question 3 is about the whole part of leaf, so you can guess that information for this question may appear in third or fourth paragraph.</p>\n\n<p>The bracket near number 3 captures the main part of the leaf. The third paragraph tells us that: The blade is the broad, flat part of the leaf.</p>\n\n<p>Thus, the correct answer is <strong>blade</strong>.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:36:40', '2017-11-15 16:36:40'),
(1361, 34, 1, 8, 182, 'petiole', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>&nbsp; Look at the picture&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>The area of some plants that <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>connects the plant&#39;s stem and leaf </strong></span>is called the petiole</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The fourth part you have to label is the part of the leaf that connects it to the plant&rsquo;s stem. And once again, you can find the answer in the highlighted sentence: petiole</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:36:40', '2017-11-15 16:36:40'),
(1362, 35, 1, 8, 183, 'rise', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>&nbsp;...<span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>different meerkat groups</strong></span><b>..............</b>at <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>different times of the day. &nbsp;</strong></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>while members of one meerkat troop</strong></span> will consistently <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">rise </span></strong><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>very early</strong></span>, <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>those of another</strong></span> will emerge from their burrows <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>much later in the morning</strong></span>.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The last sentence of first paragraph contains answer for this question. The key point to do this question is to know what is required in the blank. In this case, we need a verb, and the information for this question is about the different between members of meerkat.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:47:04', '2017-11-15 16:47:04'),
(1363, 35, 1, 8, 184, 'innovative', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>They also learned that <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>young</strong></span>, <span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>male </strong></span>meerkats were more...................than other members of their social groups when it <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>came to problem solving</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>The tests showed that the more subordinate <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>juvenile </strong></span>members of meerkat troops are the most <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">innovative</span></strong> when it comes to foraging - these low-ranking <span style=\"color:#d35400;\"><strong>males</strong></span> were best at <span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>solving problems</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>We need an adjective for this blank. Keyword for this blank is male meerkats, problem solving. We can find the information in highlighted sentences.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:47:04', '2017-11-15 16:47:04'),
(1364, 35, 1, 8, 185, 'treat', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>They were <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>rewarded </strong></span>with a<b>..............</b>.&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>.......and&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>obtaining </strong></span>the <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">treat</span></strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The answer for this blank is in the same sentence with question 2.&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:47:04', '2017-11-15 16:47:04'),
(1365, 35, 1, 8, 186, 'opaque', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>However, they also found that the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>meerkats </strong></span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>never learned </strong></span>that it was the.....................<span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><strong>part of the container that they needed to open.</strong></span></p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Dr. Thornton conceded that&nbsp;the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>meerkats </strong></span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>didn&#39;t ever appear to work out</strong></span> that it was the <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">opaque </span><span style=\"color:#2980b9;\">surface</span></strong>...&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>We need an adjective</p>\n\n<p>The information for this blank is in highlighted sentence. It is quite clear the answer is opaque</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 16:47:04', '2017-11-15 16:47:04'),
(1366, 36, 1, 8, 192, 'intake', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Reservoir </strong></span>or.......................</p>\n\n			<p>Look at the picture</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Often, this <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>reservoir </strong></span>is used as a recreational lake and is also known as the <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">intake</span></strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>In the second sentence of this passage, we can find the answer for this question.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 17:02:52', '2017-11-15 17:02:52'),
(1367, 36, 1, 8, 193, 'magnets', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p><span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>Generator </strong></span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\"><strong>containing</strong></span>.................</p>\n\n			<p>Look at the pictur</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>As the turbine blades turn, so do a series of <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">magnets </span><span style=\"color:#e67e22;\">inside </span></strong>the <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>generator </strong></span>producing alternating current [AG] by moving electrons.&nbsp;.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 17:02:52', '2017-11-15 17:02:52'),
(1368, 36, 1, 8, 194, 'powerhouse', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Look at the picture&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>The <span style=\"color:#1abc9c;\"><strong>transformer</strong></span>, located inside the <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">powerhouse</span></strong>...</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The answer can be found in highlighted sentence.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 17:02:52', '2017-11-15 17:02:52'),
(1369, 36, 1, 8, 195, 'shaft', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>Look at the picture&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>The water strikes and turns the large blades of a turbine, which is attached to a generator above it by way of&nbsp;a <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">shaft</span></strong></p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Just take a look at the picture, we can see that question 4 and 5, they are related to the process when water come into the turbine.</p>\n\n<p>So, focus on the midle area of this paragraph to find the answer for this question. And the answer must be something related to turbine. We</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 17:02:52', '2017-11-15 17:02:52'),
(1370, 36, 1, 8, 196, 'penstock', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"explanation-table-custom\" style=\"width:100%;\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Words in question</td>\n			<td>Similar words in passage</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<p>&nbsp;Look at the picture&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<p>Gates on the dam open and gravity pulls the water through the <strong><span style=\"background-color:#ecf0f1;\">penstock</span></strong>.</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>The answer of this question must be related to the Gate. So, we can easily find the information in hihglighted sentence.</p>\n', 1, '2017-11-15 17:02:52', '2017-11-15 17:02:52');
